Review: This film smokes rocks. At first it seemingly had no self awareness, but the bigger it got the more I submitted. This movie is positively wylin. With shades of Of Mice & Men and Altered States. A man with the “mental capabilities of a 6 year old” consumes enough information (via a 1992 VR headset) to become some sort of hyper intelligent multi-dimensional being, graduating from mind reading, to telepathy, to reassembling a man’s particles.I watched the Director’s Cut, which…

Movie: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King

Review: There’s even less of a story here than there is in the first, but I still found myself enjoying it more. The action sequences alone are worth the viewing, and undoubtedly the best CGI I’ve ever seen. Just a beautiful movie to look at, even if it does feel like a 3 hour ad for a Sandals Resort (all it’s missing is a One Republic accompaniment).
“Fuego basura… is that how you say ‘dumpster fire’ in Spanish?”
